cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "Sessions Are Braids: Measuring Latent Thread Structure in Real Coding-Agent Sessions"
abstract: >-
  A measurement note on real coding-agent sessions: what the context window is made of
  by turn intent and by latent topic structure, evidence that sessions interleave
  multiple threads, and a component analysis of what condensation must preserve when
  context is scoped to a thread.
